# -*- mode:org;coding:utf-8 -*-
#+TITLE: look for on-demand macOS and windows cloud runners
#+AUTHOR: Pascal J. Bourguignon
#+DATE: 2026-07-23

The macOS (thalassa) and ms-windows (PC) runners are intermittent
laptops. The platform test lanes (test:clautolisp:{macos,windows},
verify:vl-registry:{macos,windows}) proved their worth on day one —
five genuine platform bugs — so reliable capacity is wanted.

* Task (pjb)

Survey cloud runner options usable on demand from gitlab.com CI:

- macOS: GitLab SaaS macOS runners (premium tiers), MacStadium/Orka,
  AWS EC2 Mac instances, Scaleway Apple silicon — pricing per job
  minute vs a reserved instance; arm64 (Apple silicon) preferred to
  match thalassa.
- windows: GitLab SaaS windows runners, a small always-on VM (Azure /
  Hetzner / OVH) with gitlab-runner as a service, shell = powershell.
- Requirements either way: sbcl + quicklisp installable at job time or
  baked into an image; tags to keep: [macos, arm64, shell] /
  [windows, amd64, shell] so the existing lanes pick them up
  unchanged; cost gate (manual trigger or scheduled) acceptable.

When one is adopted, consider promoting the platform lanes from
allow_failure to blocking on release tags.
